[1] Minas Gerais state
Date: Wed 11 Jan 2017
Source: G1 [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
http://g1.globo.com/minas-gerais/noticia/minas-gerais-tem-48-casos-suspeitos-de-febre-amarela-diz-secretaria.ghtml


Minas Gerais has 48 suspected yellow fever cases, says the Secretariat
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The Minas Gerais state Secretariat of Health stated on this Wed 11 [Jan 2017] that the number of suspected cases of yellow fever increased to 48. Of these cases, 16 are considered probable since the patients presented with the criteria for suspected cases, according to the Health Surveillance Guide, and had preliminary positive laboratory results. Confirmation still depends on more investigation.

The cities with most probable cases among these 16 are de Minas, with 3, and Caratinga, Ubaporanga and Ipanema with 2. Also there are probable cases registered in the cities of Inhapim, Piedade de Caratinga and São Domingo das Dores, Itambacuri, all in the Rio Doce Valley; and Frei Gaspar, Ladainha and Poté, in the Mucuri Valley.

Currently, the city with the most suspected cases of the 48 reported is Ladainha with 10, followed by Caratinga and Piedade do Caratinga with 6 in each city.

Of the 14 deaths suspected due to the disease, 8 are considered probable, according to the Secretariat. That is to say they have had positive tests and other factors that are still being investigated.

In Entre Folhas and São Sebastião do Maranhão, both in the Rio Doce Valley, no probable cases were registered, but there were cases of dead and ill monkeys registered.

The Secretariat stated also that the transmission in the rural area is related to the _Haemagogus_ mosquito. Yellow fever [virus] is also transmitted by _Aedes aegypti_, but just in urban environments. There have been no investigated cases in urban areas.

Notification began on this past 5 [Jan 2017]. The Secretariat issued an alert for those traveling to those cities to be current for vaccination. Also said was that the vaccine is available and resupply has now been requested from the Ministry of Health.

The last case of rural [sylvan] yellow fever was registered in Minas Gerais in 2009, with no urban cases since 1942, according to the agency.

The Ministry of Health reported that 450 000 doses of vaccine against yellow fever will be sent to Minas Gerais this Thursday [12 Jan 2017].

The governments of Ladainha and Teófilo Otoni declared a state of emergency due to the suspected cases of the disease.

The government of the state published this Thursday (12 [Jan 2017]) a decree creating a situation room in order to monitor the cases of yellow fever in Minas Gerais. A committee will be composed of representatives of Civil Defense, the State Secretariat of Health, the Ministry of Health, Government Secretariat and the State Secretariat of the Environment.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed-port@promedmail.org>

[Fortunately, so far all cases have been spill-over from the sylvan (forest) cycle of transmission and not person-mosquito-person in an urban cycle. However, there is the risk that one of these individuals might arrive in an urban setting while viremic, triggering an urban cycle should both _Aedes aegypti_ and unvaccinated individuals be present, as occurred in Paraguay in 2008. The concern expressed for and actions taken by the health agencies is justified. - Mod.TY

Maps of Brazil can be accessed at http://s13.postimg.org/jumnalk87/map_of_Brazil.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4761705,4517.]

